        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer607076311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12274841809122351707"><b>*Last book of 2019!*</b><br/><br/>I would rate the different essays from 2 to 5 stars, so I think 3.5 is a fair rating for the whole book. Some really entertained me while others left me indifferent. <br/><br/>My favorites are Marrying Libraries, Nothing New Under the Sun (interesting facts about plagiarism), My Odd Shelf and Never Do That to a Book. In this last one, Fadiman says that we should not take excessive care of physical books (I know I do sometimes), so I&apos;m glad I read it laying in the sand under a light rai</span>
  <span id="freeText12274841809122351707" style="display:none"><b>*Last book of 2019!*</b><br /><br />I would rate the different essays from 2 to 5 stars, so I think 3.5 is a fair rating for the whole book. Some really entertained me while others left me indifferent. <br /><br />My favorites are Marrying Libraries, Nothing New Under the Sun (interesting facts about plagiarism), My Odd Shelf and Never Do That to a Book. In this last one, Fadiman says that we should not take excessive care of physical books (I know I do sometimes), so I'm glad I read it laying in the sand under a light rain. I would usually have hidden it to protect it, but it's true that the different signs of wear all tell a story!<br /><br /><b>All in all, some nice reflections but not my favorite book about books.</b></span>
